import{_ as e,c as a,o as r,d as o}from"./app.86d6c556.js";const g='{"title":"Vistas y Componentes","description":"","frontmatter":{},"headers":[{"level":2,"title":"Componente de Registro","slug":"componente-de-registro"},{"level":2,"title":"Componente de Inicio de Sesi\xF3n","slug":"componente-de-inicio-de-sesion"},{"level":2,"title":"Componente de Cierre de Sesi\xF3n","slug":"componente-de-cierre-de-sesion"},{"level":2,"title":"Vista de Tablero (Ruta Protegida)","slug":"vista-de-tablero-ruta-protegida"},{"level":2,"title":"Forgot Password View","slug":"forgot-password-view"},{"level":2,"title":"Reset Password View","slug":"reset-password-view"},{"level":2,"title":"Update Password Component","slug":"update-password-component"},{"level":2,"title":"Email Verification","slug":"email-verification"},{"level":2,"title":"Flash Message Component","slug":"flash-message-component"}],"relativePath":"vue/views- and-components.md"}',t={},i=o('<h1 id="vistas-y-componentes" tabindex="-1">Vistas y Componentes <a class="header-anchor" href="#vistas-y-componentes" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h1><p>Aqu\xED hay un desglose de cada uno de los componentes y vistas de Vue que se utilizan para gestionar la autenticaci\xF3n de usuarios, el restablecimiento de contrase\xF1as y la verificaci\xF3n de correo electr\xF3nico.</p><h2 id="componente-de-registro" tabindex="-1">Componente de Registro <a class="header-anchor" href="#componente-de-registro" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/CaribesTIC/vue-frontend-ts/blob/main/src/modules/Auth/views/Register/Index.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ver archivo en GitHub</a></p><p>El componente de registro permite a los usuarios registrarse para obtener una cuenta si no tienen una. Funciona con el punto final <code>/register</code> de Fortify. Solo funciona cuando un usuario no ha iniciado sesi\xF3n, no puede usarlo para agregar usuarios si ha iniciado sesi\xF3n. Para agregar usuarios a trav\xE9s de una pantalla de administraci\xF3n, necesitar\xEDamos crear otro punto final de API y modificar este componente para publicarlo tambi\xE9n. Por ahora, se mantiene simplemente para registrar nuevos usuarios. Una vez que un usuario se registra correctamente, inicia sesi\xF3n autom\xE1ticamente y se le redirige al panel.</p><h2 id="componente-de-inicio-de-sesion" tabindex="-1">Componente de Inicio de Sesi\xF3n <a class="header-anchor" href="#componente-de-inicio-de-sesion" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/CaribesTIC/vue-frontend-ts/blob/main/src/modules/Auth/views/Login/Index.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ver archivo en GitHub</a></p><p>El formulario de inicio de sesi\xF3n funciona con el punto final <code>/login</code> de Fortify. Tenga en cuenta que todos los puntos finales se mantienen en el m\xF3dulo <code>AuthService</code> que se importa en cada <code>view/component</code>. Una vez que un usuario inicia sesi\xF3n correctamente, se le redirige al panel de control.</p><h2 id="componente-de-cierre-de-sesion" tabindex="-1">Componente de Cierre de Sesi\xF3n <a class="header-anchor" href="#componente-de-cierre-de-sesion" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/CaribesTIC/vue-frontend-ts/blob/main/src/components/Logout.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ver archivo en GitHub</a></p><p>Un componente simple que funciona con el punto final <code>/logout</code> de Fortify. Cuando se cierra la sesi\xF3n de un usuario, se env\xEDa la acci\xF3n de <code>authStore.logout()</code> que borra al usuario del <code>Store</code> y lo redirige a la vista de inicio de sesi\xF3n.</p><h2 id="vista-de-tablero-ruta-protegida" tabindex="-1">Vista de Tablero (Ruta Protegida) <a class="header-anchor" href="#vista-de-tablero-ruta-protegida" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/CaribesTIC/vue-frontend-ts/blob/main/src/modules/Auth/views/Dashboard/Index.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Ver archivo en GitHub</a></p><p>Este componente requiere autenticaci\xF3n antes de que pueda verse. Un tablero podr\xEDa mostrar mucho m\xE1s, pero lo importante aqu\xED es que est\xE1 protegido. Un usuario debe estar registrado para verlo.</p><h2 id="forgot-password-view" tabindex="-1">Forgot Password View <a class="header-anchor" href="#forgot-password-view" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/garethredfern/laravel-vue/blob/main/src/views/ForgotPassword.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View file on GitHub</a></p><p>The forgot password view can be accessed if a user is not logged in and needs to reset their password. It works with the Fortify /forgot-password endpoint. Once the form is submitted Laravel will check the email is valid and send out a reset password email. The link in this email will have a token and the URL will point to the reset password view in the SPA.</p><h2 id="reset-password-view" tabindex="-1">Reset Password View <a class="header-anchor" href="#reset-password-view" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/garethredfern/laravel-vue/blob/main/src/views/ResetPassword.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View file on GitHub</a></p><p>The reset password view displays a form where a user can change their password. Importantly it will also have access to the token provided by Laravel. It works with the Fortify /reset-password endpoint. When the form is submitted the users email and token are checked by Laravel. If everything was successful, a message is displayed and the user can log in.</p><h2 id="update-password-component" tabindex="-1">Update Password Component <a class="header-anchor" href="#update-password-component" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/garethredfern/laravel-vue/blob/main/src/components/UpdatePassword.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View file on GitHub</a></p><p>This form allows a logged-in user to update their password. It works with the Fortify /user/password endpoint.</p><h2 id="email-verification" tabindex="-1">Email Verification <a class="header-anchor" href="#email-verification" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/garethredfern/laravel-vue/blob/main/src/components/VerifyEmail.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View file on GitHub</a></p><p>Laravel provides the ability for a user to verify their email as an added layer of security. This component works with the /email/verification-notification endpoint. To get the email notification working, there is some set up required within the Laravel API. More detail in these instructions.</p><p>With this in place, the SPA will check a user is verified using the details in the auth Vuex store. If they are not, a button is displayed, when clicked the verification email will be sent by Laravel. The email will have a link to verify and return the user back to the SPA dashboard.</p><h2 id="flash-message-component" tabindex="-1">Flash Message Component <a class="header-anchor" href="#flash-message-component" aria-hidden="true">#</a></h2><p><a href="https://github.com/garethredfern/laravel-vue/blob/main/src/components/FlashMessage.vue" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">View file on GitHub</a></p><p>While the user is interacting with the API via the SPA we need to give them success and error messages. The Laravel API will be handling a lot of these messages, but we can also use catch try/catch blocks to display messages within the SPA. To keep things all in one place there is a FlashMessage component which takes a message and error prop.</p>',30),n=[i];function s(d,l,c,h,p,u){return r(),a("div",null,n)}var f=e(t,[["render",s]]);export{g as __pageData,f as default};
